  "prompt": "What is my Asian size if I'm XS in the U.S.?",
  "response": "Asian sizing can differ significantly from US sizing, and it often varies from country to country within Asia. Generally, Asian sizes are smaller than US sizes. If you\u2019re an XS in the US, you might typically be a Small (S) or Medium (M) in Asian sizes, depending on the specific country's sizing standards. \n\nHere is a rough guide:\n\n- **China/Japan/Korea:** If you\u2019re an XS in the US, you might be a Medium (M) or Large (L) in these countries.\n- **India:** Sizing can be similar to US sizes, so you might still be an XS or S.\n\nIt\u2019s always best to check the specific size charts provided by the brand or retailer, as sizes can vary widely even within the same country.",
